First of all I, love building antennas, small magnetic loops, Beverage and
such and I'm eager to learn from the experts with a lifetime of experience
in the antenna field.

With this ferrite topic  the discussion deteriorated to what I call a clash
of the giants, very much of the ego playing and not much information coming
out of these heated discussions.

My question to the experts out there is simple.

If I have an air wound coil and that is my antenna to gather the
electromagnetic field to be processed  as voltage in my RF amplifier, will
the insertion of a ferromagnetic stick into the coil enhance the incoming
signal voltage.

I forget which of the two Alan's mentioned it, but to detect an EMF at 10 KHz
is  an excellent achievement indeed.

